 Again My Life

6
00:00:00,150 --> 00:00:03,930
 Episode 11

7
00:00:03,930 --> 00:00:06,940
- Assemblyman Jo Tae Seop came to see him?
 - Yes.

8
00:00:11,530 --> 00:00:13,160
 Cheonha Hospital

9
00:00:18,620 --> 00:00:22,050
 He needs to rest as much as possible.

10
00:00:22,050 --> 00:00:25,650
 If anything were to cause a shock to his heart...

11
00:00:33,370 --> 00:00:35,930
 Wishing you a speedy recovery

12
00:00:37,870 --> 00:00:41,270
Vice-Chairman Kim Yong Jun came to see me.

13
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:46,400
He grew up well. He has good reasoning skills.

14
00:00:46,400 --> 00:00:51,350
He asked me to help him become the chairman in exchange for handing me the outlet.

15
00:00:51,350 --> 00:00:55,690
The ability to figure out who he's dealing with,

16
00:00:55,690 --> 00:00:58,460
it's a virtue businessmen need.

17
00:00:58,460 --> 00:01:00,520
So I came to the conclusion

18
00:01:00,520 --> 00:01:05,320
that I can leave Cheonha to Vice-Chairman Kim Yong Joon.

19
00:01:06,630 --> 00:01:10,670
Assemblyman Jo, that's my decision.

20
00:01:10,670 --> 00:01:12,430
In time, the successor issue will be—

21
00:01:12,430 --> 00:01:16,250
As you get older, your judgment becomes blurred.

22
00:01:16,250 --> 00:01:18,290
I guess that's why you don't realize

23
00:01:18,290 --> 00:01:19,680
the time has come for you to step away.

24
00:01:19,680 --> 00:01:21,970
- Assemblyman Jo!
 - Chairman.

25
00:01:22,740 --> 00:01:26,740
You should step down now.

26
00:01:26,740 --> 00:01:31,230
Cheonha needs to start a new era now.

27
00:01:31,960 --> 00:01:34,260
 Rehabilitation Center

28
00:01:34,260 --> 00:01:38,650
Check and see if Oppa and Seung Jun made contact with Assemblyman Jo Tae Seop.

29
00:01:38,650 --> 00:01:42,570
- Also, find out what the board members have been up to.
 - Yes.

30
00:01:44,470 --> 00:01:46,030
Jo Tae Seop...

31
00:01:46,030 --> 00:01:47,900
That's right.

32
00:01:47,900 --> 00:01:51,770
Thanks to Cheonha, Korea has made great progress.

33
00:01:51,770 --> 00:01:53,880
I acknowledge that.

34
00:01:53,880 --> 00:02:00,020
But we can no longer keep up with the times with your vision.

35
00:02:01,730 --> 00:02:03,830
I guess you don't know.

36
00:02:03,830 --> 00:02:08,350
Cheonha will never operate on the opinions of a chairman alone.

37
00:02:08,350 --> 00:02:12,880
But it is the sole chairman who makes the decisions.

38
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:16,940
The general election is around the corner,

39
00:02:16,940 --> 00:02:23,330
so why don't you concentrate on that? I'll worry about my company.

40
00:02:24,960 --> 00:02:30,170
I think you misunderstand me.

41
00:02:30,170 --> 00:02:34,130
I, Jo Tae Seop, think only about this country's future.

42
00:02:35,560 --> 00:02:37,680
You mean your own future.

43
00:02:37,680 --> 00:02:40,400
Not at all. You're mistaken.

44
00:02:40,400 --> 00:02:43,380
Then let me ask.

45
00:02:43,380 --> 00:02:47,700
What do you think about Hui Ah as my successor?

46
00:02:50,900 --> 00:02:53,020
You probably don't like that

47
00:02:53,020 --> 00:02:57,200
since she would never follow your wishes.

48
00:02:57,200 --> 00:03:00,790
What you want isn't Korea's future.

49
00:03:00,790 --> 00:03:04,500
What you want is a dog that obeys.

50
00:03:07,930 --> 00:03:12,670
I thought you wouldn't understand, so I prepared a gift.

51
00:03:17,990 --> 00:03:19,510
 Let's move onto the next story.

52
00:03:19,510 --> 00:03:23,000
 Kim Geon Yeong, chairman of Cheonha Group, who had been rumored to be ill,

53
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:25,710
  has been hospitalized for 15 days, it has been confirmed.

54
00:03:25,710 --> 00:03:29,110
- I've laid the groundwork.
 -  According to an official from the Cheonha Group,

55
00:03:31,630 --> 00:03:33,270
- Chairman.
 -  he's is critical condition.

56
00:03:36,530 --> 00:03:39,090
Come down on your own.

57
00:03:39,940 --> 00:03:44,580
There's nothing more miserable than being dragged down.

58
00:03:47,840 --> 00:03:52,220
Is the gift you prepared... merely this?

59
00:03:52,220 --> 00:03:55,270
I thought you were coming with a fruit basket,

60
00:03:55,270 --> 00:03:57,440
but you came holding a knife.

61
00:03:58,220 --> 00:04:04,790
But you should know, too. I also have a knife.

62
00:04:08,560 --> 00:04:11,030
 - Move aside!
 - You can't go in!

63
00:04:15,090 --> 00:04:17,100
- They're in the middle of a conversation.
 - Move aside.

64
00:04:17,100 --> 00:04:19,590
I told you they're having a conversation.

65
00:04:21,700 --> 00:04:23,460
Let her in.

66
00:04:30,730 --> 00:04:33,320
It's nice to see you, Miss Hui Ah.

67
00:04:38,460 --> 00:04:40,100
Let's go.

68
00:04:44,140 --> 00:04:46,850
 Chairman Kim's critical condition...

69
00:04:49,840 --> 00:04:52,020
Dad, are you okay?

70
00:04:52,020 --> 00:04:54,240
Don't worry.

71
00:04:54,240 --> 00:04:56,700
I'm sure he came to see you on purpose.

72
00:04:56,700 --> 00:04:59,860
He must have been the one who leaked it to the media, too.

73
00:05:01,230 --> 00:05:03,890
What did he want this time?

74
00:05:03,890 --> 00:05:06,160
You don't need to know.

75
00:05:06,160 --> 00:05:10,390
Everything is up to me to figure out before I go.

76
00:05:13,810 --> 00:05:15,650
 Cheonha Hospital

77
00:05:15,650 --> 00:05:18,950
- How was the visit?
 - How is he feeling?

78
00:05:18,950 --> 00:05:22,160
What did you talk about?

79
00:05:22,160 --> 00:05:25,680
Please answer a few questions!

80
00:05:29,830 --> 00:05:31,500
Let's go.

81
00:05:31,500 --> 00:05:33,670
Please give us a statement!

82
00:05:34,730 --> 00:05:37,090
 We heard that you went to visit Chairman Kim Geon Yeong at the hospital.

83
00:05:37,090 --> 00:05:39,280
- Hello.
 - Hi.
 -  What did you talk about?

84
00:05:39,280 --> 00:05:41,140
 I'm sorry.

85
00:05:41,140 --> 00:05:43,960
 I can't speak about it.

86
00:05:43,960 --> 00:05:46,520
 How is Chairman Kim Geon Yeong feeling?

87
00:05:46,520 --> 00:05:49,450
 As a citizen,

88
00:05:49,450 --> 00:05:54,710
 Chairman Kim Geon Yeong is someone I respect, and I can only wish for his speedy recovery.

89
00:05:54,710 --> 00:05:56,910
 Chairman Kim is critically ill...

90
00:05:56,910 --> 00:05:59,450
 That's why Hui Ah...

91
00:05:59,450 --> 00:06:03,810
 A monk cuts his hair when he leaves the world, right?

92
00:06:04,800 --> 00:06:07,070
 I came to cut my hair, too.

93
00:06:23,150 --> 00:06:25,270
 Hui Ah has jumped into management.

94
00:06:25,270 --> 00:06:28,050
 It's a different development from my previous life.

95
00:06:28,740 --> 00:06:31,610
Did you really meet with Assemblyman Jo Tae Seop?

96
00:06:31,610 --> 00:06:35,080
Yes, I did. I gave him the outlet, too.

97
00:06:36,360 --> 00:06:38,310
But Dad told you.

98
00:06:38,310 --> 00:06:40,830
To develop the outlet on your own steam.

99
00:06:40,830 --> 00:06:43,040
Never to have involvement with the political world.

100
00:06:43,040 --> 00:06:46,320
- It's cooperation, not involvement.
 - Oppa!

101
00:06:46,320 --> 00:06:49,890
Why? Should I shovel and lay the bricks myself, too?

102
00:06:49,890 --> 00:06:51,700
You don't live alone in this world.

103
00:06:51,700 --> 00:06:54,620
You know how Jo Tae Seop thinks.

104
00:06:54,620 --> 00:06:56,240
He'll put you on a leash.

105
00:06:56,240 --> 00:06:58,380
That's for me to worry about.

106
00:06:59,240 --> 00:07:00,910
And he'll shake up Cheonha Group.

107
00:07:00,910 --> 00:07:03,550
I'll worry about that.

108
00:07:04,910 --> 00:07:06,700
Kim Hui Ah,

109
00:07:06,700 --> 00:07:11,970
stay quietly if you don't want to get kicked out and lose everything you have.

110
00:07:19,330 --> 00:07:21,400
I've contacted the board of Cheonha Group

111
00:07:21,400 --> 00:07:25,180
that you'll support Vice-Chairman Kim Yong Jun.

112
00:07:25,180 --> 00:07:29,330
Then we'll now begin working on his image.

113
00:07:30,820 --> 00:07:33,050
 An Anonymous Donor Angel

114
00:07:33,050 --> 00:07:34,610
Okay.

115
00:07:35,670 --> 00:07:37,410
Sir.

116
00:07:37,410 --> 00:07:40,010
What should we do about Jo Yun Ah?

117
00:07:40,010 --> 00:07:41,900
Jo Yun Ah...

118
00:07:47,990 --> 00:07:49,610
Yes, sir.

119
00:07:56,710 --> 00:07:58,530
Who are you?

120
00:08:01,020 --> 00:08:03,010
What are you?

121
00:08:19,870 --> 00:08:23,990
 The actress Jo Yun Ah died in her home last night.

122
00:08:23,990 --> 00:08:29,530
 The late Jo Yun Ah, who appeared like a comet in 2009 and swept the rookie awards at various film festivals,

123
00:08:29,530 --> 00:08:32,480
 had recently signed with a major US agency

124
00:08:32,480 --> 00:08:34,680
 and was about to enter Hollywood,

125
00:08:34,680 --> 00:08:38,180
 adding to her fans' sadness.

126
00:08:40,570 --> 00:08:43,520
"Everything has happened because of money.

127
00:08:43,520 --> 00:08:46,130
"I didn't know things would get so big.

128
00:08:46,130 --> 00:08:47,610
"There are no videos.

129
00:08:47,610 --> 00:08:50,600
"I apologize to President Choi Su Hyeok and to Vice Chairman Kim Yong Jun.

130
00:08:50,600 --> 00:08:51,660
"I'm sorry.

131
00:08:51,660 --> 00:08:55,720
"I take responsibility for everything as I leave."

132
00:08:55,720 --> 00:08:58,030
This is too perfect a suicide note.

133
00:08:58,030 --> 00:09:01,570
Not to mention the cause of death. Overdosing on methamphetamine while drinking!

134
00:09:01,570 --> 00:09:06,350
Did she use methamphetamine, too? Wasn't it propofol that she was using?

135
00:09:06,350 --> 00:09:09,510
I feel like I've seen this before.

136
00:09:13,720 --> 00:09:17,700
 It's just the right mix of alcohol and methamphetamine.

137
00:09:18,540 --> 00:09:20,330
Where?

138
00:09:23,880 --> 00:09:25,590
Never mind.

139
00:09:25,590 --> 00:09:27,790
What's with you?

140
00:09:29,030 --> 00:09:30,790
Take a look.

141
00:09:40,240 --> 00:09:43,480
 Actress Jo Yun Ah's "Suicide"
 Leaves a Suicide Note On the Recent Controversy

142
00:09:49,230 --> 00:09:51,440
 Actress Jo Yoon Ah's "Suicide"
 Leaves a Suicide Note On the Recent Controversy

143
00:09:51,440 --> 00:09:53,370
 ... drinking when it's not enough, will it fill that void?

144
00:09:53,370 --> 00:09:55,460
Yes, I understand.

145
00:09:57,160 --> 00:09:59,940
That was from Vice-Chairman Kim Yong Jun's office.

146
00:09:59,940 --> 00:10:02,890
With regard to the instructions you gave on Cheonha Distribution,

147
00:10:02,890 --> 00:10:05,230
he agreed that there will be no restructuring between labor and management

148
00:10:05,230 --> 00:10:09,170
and that he will take the lead in hiring more young people.

149
00:10:09,970 --> 00:10:12,390
He understands quickly.

150
00:10:12,390 --> 00:10:16,630
And the site of the outlet was also confirmed and announced as the area you proposed

151
00:10:16,630 --> 00:10:18,830
to Chairman Kim Geon Yeong in the past.

152
00:10:18,830 --> 00:10:22,260
It's commendable. Good.

153
00:10:22,260 --> 00:10:24,900
Then I'll have to reciprocate.

154
00:10:24,900 --> 00:10:27,580
I can't let him remain in his father's shadow forever.

155
00:10:27,580 --> 00:10:30,530
Put in a call to Chief Prosecutor Kim Seok Hun.

156
00:10:30,530 --> 00:10:32,410
I understand.

157
00:10:42,100 --> 00:10:44,420
Why aren't you answering your calls?

158
00:10:44,420 --> 00:10:46,280
Chief wants to see us.

159
00:11:08,690 --> 00:11:14,270
Chairman Kim Geon Yeong of Cheonha Group is in critical condition, and the succession process is marred by expediency.

160
00:11:14,270 --> 00:11:17,670
You will become righteous prosecutors from this moment on.

161
00:11:17,670 --> 00:11:20,320
If there's any punk here who received an allowance from Cheonha Group,

162
00:11:20,320 --> 00:11:25,720
remove all evidence of it, and if any of you have friends there, forget them.

163
00:11:25,720 --> 00:11:28,720
You will only look at the crime.

164
00:11:28,720 --> 00:11:31,550
Show the world that the law is fair!

165
00:11:31,550 --> 00:11:33,420
- Got it?
 - Yes, sir!

166
00:11:33,420 --> 00:11:34,920
That's all.

167
00:11:34,920 --> 00:11:38,810
 Special Investigation Team Office

168
00:11:43,310 --> 00:11:49,310
 Special independent Prosecutor Choi Kang Jin

169
00:11:51,790 --> 00:11:54,950
Turn in your cellphones, and don't answer any calls!

170
00:11:54,950 --> 00:11:58,670
Track down borrowed-name accounts of former and current employees

171
00:11:58,670 --> 00:12:02,700
and shake down every Cheonha Group affiliate who has securities accounts and trades stock.

172
00:12:02,700 --> 00:12:04,660
 Yes, sir!

173
00:12:04,660 --> 00:12:07,650
- What? The prosecution?
 - Yes.

174
00:12:07,650 --> 00:12:12,980
They're investigating the overall succession process and the three of us, too.

175
00:12:18,900 --> 00:12:21,130
 Chairman Kim Geon Yeon will think

176
00:12:21,130 --> 00:12:24,090
 that the prosecution is gunning for him.

177
00:12:24,090 --> 00:12:25,930
 But...

178
00:12:32,450 --> 00:12:38,300
if you scar a healthy body, it loses its overall value.

179
00:12:38,300 --> 00:12:41,590
You just need to get rid of the one thing that's ruining the balance.

180
00:12:47,950 --> 00:12:49,620
Like this.

181
00:12:50,610 --> 00:12:54,420
How is it? Doesn't it look good?

182
00:12:57,720 --> 00:12:59,560
Sir.

183
00:13:01,230 --> 00:13:03,090
Mr. Kim Seong Jun?

184
00:13:03,090 --> 00:13:05,250
What is it?

185
00:13:05,250 --> 00:13:08,070
I'm Prosecutor Choi Kang Jin from the Central District Office.

186
00:13:09,740 --> 00:13:13,880
I'd like to give you a choice. Would you cooperate and come with us quietly?

187
00:13:13,880 --> 00:13:16,520
Or do you want your face all over the news?

188
00:13:16,520 --> 00:13:19,320
- What?
 - Let's go.

189
00:13:19,320 --> 00:13:21,420
- Seong Jun?
- Yes, sir.

190
00:13:21,420 --> 00:13:25,040
It looks like he committed embezzlement.

191
00:13:25,040 --> 00:13:30,330
 Kim Geon Yeong will know that Seong Jun's arrest is a warning.

192
00:13:32,450 --> 00:13:34,080
Dad.

193
00:13:38,570 --> 00:13:41,590
I'll bring Seong Jun back.

194
00:13:41,590 --> 00:13:44,890
 And that the next target is Kim Hui Ah.

195
00:13:44,890 --> 00:13:46,940
I'll take care of everything, so you stay out of this.

196
00:13:46,940 --> 00:13:50,850
I told you that I must put an end to this with my own hands.

197
00:13:50,850 --> 00:13:52,730
Dad.

198
00:13:56,810 --> 00:13:59,610
No, don't cut it too close.

199
00:13:59,610 --> 00:14:01,820
Yes, sir.

200
00:14:01,820 --> 00:14:04,480
Good. That's it.

201
00:14:04,480 --> 00:14:09,610
Great. Get ready to greet a guest.

202
00:14:10,820 --> 00:14:15,680
Chairman Kim Geon Yeong won't surrender like this.

203
00:14:15,680 --> 00:14:19,650
He'll visit me with a knife in his hand.

204
00:14:22,780 --> 00:14:24,320
Okay.

205
00:14:28,430 --> 00:14:31,940
Sir, Chairman Kim Geon Yeong is here.

206
00:14:37,690 --> 00:14:42,320
 Again My Life

207
00:14:47,860 --> 00:14:50,140
What brings you here?

208
00:15:02,820 --> 00:15:05,440
What are you doing?

209
00:15:05,440 --> 00:15:09,900
My son, Seong Jun. Please let him go.

210
00:15:09,900 --> 00:15:13,430
Yong Jun, Seong Jun, and Hui Ah.

211
00:15:13,430 --> 00:15:15,830
I do not want my children...

212
00:15:16,590 --> 00:15:21,410
to be involved any further in political circles.

213
00:15:21,410 --> 00:15:22,860
Chairman Kim.

214
00:15:22,860 --> 00:15:25,970
Please, this is my last wish.

215
00:15:25,970 --> 00:15:31,860
I want this relationship to end with me.

216
00:15:35,690 --> 00:15:39,960
I'm sorry. I'm afraid I can't grant your wish.

217
00:16:00,520 --> 00:16:04,720
 You'll just serve ten years in jail, no more.

218
00:16:04,720 --> 00:16:06,190
Chairman Kim!

